# Docker Standards

## Multi-Architecture Support

Always support both amd64 and arm64 architectures:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
RUN ARCH="$(dpkg --print-architecture)" \
    && case "${ARCH}" in \
        amd64) GO_ARCH="amd64" ;; \
        arm64) GO_ARCH="arm64" ;; \
        *) echo "Unsupported architecture: ${ARCH}" >&2; exit 1 ;; \
    esac \
    && curl -fsSL https://go.dev/dl/go${GO_VERSION}.linux-${GO_ARCH}.tar.gz -o /tmp/go.tgz
```

## Version Pinning

Pin all tool versions using ARG variables at the top:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
ARG NODE_MAJOR=20
ARG GO_VERSION=1.22.6
ARG RUST_VERSION=1.89.0
ARG TRIVY_VERSION=0.55.2
```

Use these versions consistently throughout the Dockerfile.

## Layer Optimization

Group related operations and clean up in the same layer:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
RUN apt-get update \
    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        build-essential \
        ca-certificates \
        curl \
        git \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
```

## Non-Interactive Installation

Set `DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive` to avoid prompts:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
```

## Tool Installation Patterns

### Node.js

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_${NODE_MAJOR}.x | bash - \
    && apt-get update \
    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends nodejs \
    && corepack enable \
    && corepack prepare pnpm@latest --activate \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
```

### Go

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
RUN ARCH="$(dpkg --print-architecture)" \
    && case "${ARCH}" in \
        amd64) GO_ARCH="amd64" ;; \
        arm64) GO_ARCH="arm64" ;; \
        *) echo "Unsupported architecture: ${ARCH}" >&2; exit 1 ;; \
    esac \
    && curl -fsSL https://go.dev/dl/go${GO_VERSION}.linux-${GO_ARCH}.tar.gz -o /tmp/go.tgz \
    && tar -C /usr/local -xzf /tmp/go.tgz \
    && rm /tmp/go.tgz
ENV PATH="/usr/local/go/bin:${PATH}"
RUN go install golang.org/x/vuln/cmd/govulncheck@latest
```

### Rust

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
RUN ARCH="$(dpkg --print-architecture)" \
    && case "${ARCH}" in \
        amd64) RUST_ARCH="x86_64" ;; \
        arm64) RUST_ARCH="aarch64" ;; \
        *) echo "Unsupported architecture: ${ARCH}" >&2; exit 1 ;; \
    esac \
    && curl -fsSL https://static.rust-lang.org/rustup/dist/${RUST_ARCH}-unknown-linux-gnu/rustup-init -o /tmp/rustup-init \
    && chmod +x /tmp/rustup-init \
    && /tmp/rustup-init -y --default-toolchain ${RUST_VERSION} \
    && rm /tmp/rustup-init
ENV PATH="/root/.cargo/bin:${PATH}"
RUN cargo install cargo-audit --locked --version ${CARGO_AUDIT_VERSION}
```

### Binary Downloads

For pre-built binaries, download and install directly:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
RUN ARCH="$(dpkg --print-architecture)" \
    && case "${ARCH}" in \
        amd64) TRIVY_ARCH="64bit" ;; \
        arm64) TRIVY_ARCH="ARM64" ;; \
        *) echo "Unsupported architecture: ${ARCH}" >&2; exit 1 ;; \
    esac \
    && curl -fsSL https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy/releases/download/v${TRIVY_VERSION}/trivy_${TRIVY_VERSION}_Linux-${TRIVY_ARCH}.tar.gz -o /tmp/trivy.tgz \
    && tar -xzf /tmp/trivy.tgz -C /usr/local/bin trivy \
    && rm /tmp/trivy.tgz
```

## Python Package Installation

Use `--no-cache-dir` to reduce image size:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
RUN python3 -m pip install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip \
    && python3 -m pip install --no-cache-dir semgrep checkov
```

## Docker CLI Installation

For Docker-in-Docker scenarios (Trivy scanning), install Docker CLI:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
RUN ARCH="$(dpkg --print-architecture)" \
    && curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg \
    && echo "deb [arch=${ARCH} signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable" \
        > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list \
    && apt-get update \
    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends docker-ce-cli \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
```

## Working Directory

Set WORKDIR before copying application code:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
WORKDIR /work
COPY sec_audit /work/sec_audit
```

## Entrypoint

Use Python module execution for the entrypoint:

```dockerfile
# ✅ GOOD
ENTRYPOINT ["python3", "-m", "sec_audit"]
```

This allows the container to accept CLI arguments directly.
